AGI - Spanish politics awaits with its breath the decision of the head of government, Pedro Sanchez, who will decide whether to resign or not after the news of the opening of an investigation on his wife, Begona Gòmez, accused of traffic of illicit influences. In a letter to citizens &nbsp;Stanchezza has made it known that it will suspend its institutional activities until 29 April and that by that date it will assess whether to leave its position or not. "I need to stop and reflect - said Sànchez - I must respond urgently to the question if it is worth it" to remain to the government, "despite the pantano in which the right and the extreme right are trying to transform politics".
&nbsp;
The investigation against the wife of Sànchez was opened following a complaint of the association "Manos limpias" (Mani Pulite), collective near the extreme right. In particular, according to the online media El Confidencial, the links established by Begona Gòmez with the Globalia group, sponsor of the foundation in which he worked, when Air Europa, a global airline company, was dealing with the Sànchez government to obtain public aid. Yesterday the Madrid Prosecutor asked for the closure of the investigation but the judge in charge of the case has not yet revealed his intentions.
&nbsp;
The Psoe and the Spanish left denounce a campaign of destabilization orchestrated by the right and the extreme right and of which this complaint would be the last example. The Socialists announced for tomorrow in Madrid a demonstration of support to Pedro Sànchez. Meanwhile, the reflection period announced Wednesday by the head of the Government of Madrid leaves the country, the government and the PSOE, the party of Sanchez, in complete paralysis. Both socialists and executives continue to press on Sanchez so that he does not dismiss.
&nbsp;
But at the moment no one in Spain dares to predict the decision that could take the tenant of the Moncloa. If he decides to remain in his place, he may choose to undergo a matter of trust in Parliament to prove to the opposition he enjoys the support of the majority. If he decides to resign, the early legislative elections could be undecided one year after the last elections, at the end of July. If there is still Sanchez driving the Psoe and running for Prime Minister, it is all to write.&nbsp;

